Class Offer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.shopgun.android.sdk.model.Offer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable, ICatalog<Offer>, IDealer<Offer>, IErn<Offer>, IJson<org.json.JSONObject>, IStore<Offer>, PagedPublicationOffer

    public class Offer
extends java.lang.Object
implements IErn<Offer>, IJson<org.json.JSONObject>, ICatalog<Offer>, IDealer<Offer>, IStore<Offer>, PagedPublicationOffer, android.os.Parcelable

    This class is a representation of an offer as the API v2 exposes it

    More documentation available on via our Offer Reference documentation, on the engineering blog.

      • isHotspot

        public boolean isHotspot()
        Check if this offer is from a Hotspot in a catalog.

        This isn't perfect, basically just checks if images, and links is set. So if a user sets those, this method will obviously not be correct.

        Returns:
        true if the offer is from a Hotspot else false

        public Offer setRunFrom(java.util.Date date)
